    "This statement is essentially just Corollary 2.10, but we give a detailed explanation.",
    "Theorem 6.6.",
    "Every metric 0-current in R d with compact support is a flat chain.Proof.",
    "Let K be a compact set containing the support of a metric 0-current T. The flat norm of a 0-form ω (which is merely a real-valued function) in K is equal to∥ω∥ F 0 (K) = max{∥ω∥ ∞, Lip(ω)},where the supremum and the Lipschitz constant are taken on K. By Corollary 2.10, we find a sequence of measures µ i, such that sup π |T (π) -π dµ i | → 0, where the supremum is taken over Lipschitz functions π on K with max{∥π∥ ∞, Lip(π)} ≤ 1.If we let N i be the 0-current given by forN i (ω) = ω dµ i for ω ∈ C ∞ c (R d, 0 R d) = C ∞ c (R d, R),then N i is of finite mass and therefore normal.",
    "It follows that sup∥ω∥ F 0 ≤1|T (ω) -N i (ω)| → 0, i.e."
